description:
Complete re-edit of my M16 shot HaLRGB. I wasn't happy with my previous edit at all. I had edited it on my laptop while traveling.

I have recently installed my gear into the Marathon Remote Imaging Observatory (MARIO) in Marathon, TX. I am traveling the country and controlling my system remotely from inside of my camper van. This is my first shot with data mostly gathered while on the road. All data from my own system though.

Software used to capture image:
Sequence Generator Pro
PHD2

Software used to edit:
PixInsight
Photoshop

Data gathered:
(249) Ha @ 300secs - 1x1
(130) Lum @ 45secs - 1x1
(61) R @ 60secs - 1x1
(51) G @ 60secs - 1x1
(62) B @ 60secs - 1x1

Camera : ZWO ASI1600MMPro with Gain set to 0
Telescope: William Optics GT102 W_0.8x Reducer Flattener
Mount: AP Mach1GTO
imaging_telescopes: William Optics GT102 102mm f/6.9 Apo Refractor
title: M16 - Eagle Nebula (re-edit)
